Lizeka Tandwa, News24Khusela Sangoni (ANC) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Former ANC spokesperson Keith Khoza will add muscle to the party's team in Gauteng. He joins MEC for human settlements Paul Mashatile to assist with communications in the year of municipal elections.WATCHJohannesburg - The ANC has appointed Khusela Sangoni as its new spokesperson, replacing Keith Khoza, who took up a position in the Gauteng provincial government. She was a "seasoned communicator with extensive experience in public and private sector communications and media relations", the party said in a statement on Thursday. Sangoni would work closely with the ANC NEC's sub-committee on communications and media-related policy."Sangoni is a long-standing ANC member and has served in various capacities in structures of the ANC, the ANC Youth League and the ANC Women&rsquo;s League. She is currently a member of the ANC Gauteng Provincial Executive Committee," it said.Sangoni came under fire on Twitter in March, when she downplayed EFF leader Julius Malema's receiving a BA degree from Unisa. She said the achievement was mediocre.She later tweeted an apology, saying she valued "progression of black child &amp; lifelong learning".#ANC is pleased to announce appointment of Khusela Sangoni as National Comms Manager of ANC effective today pic.twitter.com/S8l5VxnHMB&mdash; ANC (@MYANC) June 1, 2016#ANC is pleased to announce appointment of Khusela Sangoni as National Comms Manager of ANC effective today pic.twitter.com/S8l5VxnHMB24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.